RoomDescription:
This is a forest. But there is a well here.
A very ugly well that looks like it was drawn by a third grader.
Pretty cool but there isn't anything special about it.

This is a forest. With trees and stuff.
You can see more forest to the south and a meadow to the east.

This is a forest. With trees and stuff.
The bottom of a cliff is to the west and more forest all around you.

This is a forest. With trees and stuff.
You see more forest to the south and a clearing to the east of you.

A small village. There is an Inn, an Arms merchant, and a potion vender here.
It looks like a good place to recover from your journey so far.

This is a forest. With trees and stuff.
This small copse of trees is surrounded by meadows on three sides.
The mountains to the north are impassible.

This is a meadow. With grass and stuff.
Lovely flowers in this meadow.
The meadow continues east with forest in all other directions.

This is a forest. With trees and stuff.
There is a meadow to the north and a clearing to the south.
More forest in the other directions.

This is a clearing in the forest. With grass and shrubs and stuff.
Looks like a nice spot for a picnic but you have things to do.

This is a forest. With trees and stuff.
The forest keeps going to east and west with a clearing to the north.

This is a meadow. With grass and stuff.
A nice meadow as meadows go.
There is a small copse of trees to the west and more meadow to the east and south.

This is a meadow. With grass and stuff.
Kind of a crap meadow with a forest south.
Otherwise the meadow continues in other directions.

This is a forest. With trees and stuff.
More forest stretch out to the west and south.
 Meadows to the north and east.

This is a forest. With trees and stuff.
Much like other forest locations, there are lots of trees.
There is a clearing to the west but more forest in all other directions.

This is a forest. With trees and stuff.
A massive cliff looms over you to the south.
The forest continues in all other directions.

This is a meadow. With grass and stuff.
A lovely meadow with mountains on two sides.
The meadow continues south and west.

This is a meadow. With grass and stuff.
Oooh! Look at all the pretty flowers!
There is a path through the mountains to the east.

This is a meadow. With grass and stuff.
Just another meadow. More meadow to the north.
There is a forest to the west and south.

This is a forest. With trees and stuff.
It's kinda creepy here. That nice meadow is to the north.
The trees keep going south and west as far as you can see.

This is a forest. With trees and stuff.
The canopy overhead is thick enough that not much light gets to you.
Anything could be hiding in the underbrush...

A mountain path. You can see a meadow ahead.
It looks nice, you should go check that out.

You see a small pond. Too bad you can't swim.
You do take a few minutes to soak your aching feet.

A fork in the mountain path. You can see a waterfall to the north.
There is a cave to the east, and it looks like a pass out of the mountains to the west.

A narrow dirt path. There are mountains on either side.
The path continues north toward a waterfall you can just make out in the distance.
The landslide that trapped you here is in the distance to the south.

A narrow dirt path. There are mountains on either side.
The path continues north and south.

A narrow dirt path. There are mountains on either side and the path behind you was blocked by a landslide.
The path leads north.

You've entered a cave. It is kinda dark in here...
You can see a path west.
An underground tunnel much like any other. The walls appear to have been carved. Poorly.
Another section of the underground tunnel. The walls appear to have been carved. Poorly.

An underground alcove. The walls appear to have been carved. Poorly.
This looks like a dead end.

You guessed it, you're still in an underground tunnel.
These walls also appear to have been poorly carved
Still in an underground tunnel. The walls appear to have been carved very poorly.
The same underground tunnel. The same poorly carved walls.
I mean, it's a tunnel. Poorly carved rock walls.
Yep, an underground tunnel. You can guess what it looks like

An underground alcove. This one has a small puddle in the corner.
It is still a dead end.
An underground tunnel. The walls look like... rock.
<sigh> an underground tunnel. The walls appear rough... and... rocky.
A poorly carved underground tunnel. Definitely a little warmer than other areas.
A warm underground tunnel. There is a mysterious door to the south glowing with power that refuses to open no matter how much you jiggle the handle

You have entered a massive cavern. The ceiling and walls are well beyond the limits of your sight.
The heat here is maybe a little oppressive.
The mysterious door has closed behind you and is glowing again.
Checking you find it is sealed and unable to be opened.
An underground tunnel. Walls. Poorly carved. From stone.
An underground tunnel. You know what it looks like.
An underground tunnel. Is it maybe a bit warmer here?
